{"key":"processedPost-9063196","value":{"id":9063196,"first":9062990,"last":9063196,"when":1223754257,"utime":"10/11/08 10:44 PM","cleanedPost":"It looks like the start of trich.&nbsp; You can't do 'surgery' you have to toss it out.&nbsp; I've recommended against so-called microwave sterilization forever, but someone always comes along to say, \"I did it in the microwave and got a flush\", thus people keep right on screwing up their grows.&nbsp; <br />You're supposed to <i>pasteurize</i> bulk substrates at 140F to 160F for one hour.&nbsp; Taking shortcuts almost never pays off in this hobby.&nbsp; Get ready to toss it out and start over.<br />You should also use hydrated lime to adjust pH, so you can get it up to 8.5 or so to start, which prevents germination of trichoderma spores.&nbsp; With calcisand or calcium carbonate, it's nearly impossible to get your peat based casing mix above a pH of 8.<br />RR"}}